INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (169,1,'2017-10-10 15:50:46','2017-10-10 18:50:46','<strong>Sky Viewer</strong>\r\n\r\nAladin snapshot only in Firefox\r\nChange cursor type according to operation mode\r\n\r\n<strong>Target Viewer</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Pan viewer included</li>\r\n 	<li>Change cursor type according to operation mode</li>\r\n 	<li>Fix: more flexible format (spaces and integers); allows to register tables with ID as string</li>\r\n 	<li>Fix: View page objects counter</li>\r\n 	<li>Enable Explorer for coadd objects</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nNotes:\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>The limit in the number of cutouts is still under discussion with NCSA. At the moment it is hardwired to be 100 to facilitate debugging. In the future one should make this operation more flexible by perhaps either choosing the number or allow the selection of individual entries</li>\r\n 	<li>At the moment cutouts for fields located between 180 and 360 are not working because of convention problems between the portal and Descut</li>\r\n</ol>','Release v0.10','','publish','open','open','','release-v0-10','','https://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu/dri/apps/home/release-note-2/\nhttps://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu/dri/apps/home/release-note/','2017-11-14 17:27:25','2017-11-14 19:27:25','',0,'http://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu/?p=169',0,'post','',0),(89,1,'2017-08-11 12:59:27','2017-08-11 15:59:27','[embed]https://youtu.be/osiGRNlMIT0[/embed]\r\n<p class=\"app-paragrafo1\">Manage lists of targets with image display, cutouts, ranking and reject functionalities. <a href=\"http://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu/dri/apps/target\" target=\"_self\">click here</a></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"app-paragrafo2\">The main functionalities of the Target viewer are:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"app-paragrafo2\">\r\n 	<li>Manage lists of targets</li>\r\n 	<li>Ability to upload</li>\r\n 	<li>Image preview</li>\r\n 	<li>List and Mosaic visualization</li>\r\n 	<li>Ranking and reject</li>\r\n 	<li>Ability to make FITS and PNG cutouts</li>\r\n 	<li>SAbility to export target lists and cutouts</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"app-paragrafo2\">Target Viewer has an extension called Target Properties based on the type of target. For instance for a Galaxy Cluster target, we can overlay a circle representing its virial radius or overlay X-Ray contours, etc.</p>','Target Viewer','http://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu:8080/dri/apps/target','inherit','closed','closed','','10-revision-v1','','','2017-08-11 12:59:27','2017-08-11 15:59:27','',10,'http://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu//10-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(82,1,'2017-07-20 11:00:49','2017-07-20 14:00:49','In Construction.','Catalog Builder','#','inherit','closed','closed','','28-revision-v1','','','2017-07-20 11:00:49','2017-07-20 14:00:49','',28,'http://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu//28-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(87,1,'2017-08-10 16:48:19','2017-08-10 19:48:19','[si-contact-form form=\'1\']','Contact US','','inherit','closed','closed','','84-revision-v1','','','2017-08-10 16:48:19','2017-08-10 19:48:19','',84,'http://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu//84-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(88,1,'2017-08-11 12:58:03','2017-08-11 15:58:03','[embed]https://youtu.be/n6POra35pwc[/embed]\r\n<p class=\"app-paragrafo1\">All-sky visualization of DES releases in grizY and RGB with overlay of tile grid and objects <a href=\"http://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu/dri/apps/sky/\" target=\"_self\">click here</a></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"app-paragrafo2\">The main functionalities are:</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Footprint</h2>\r\n<ul class=\"app-paragrafo2\">\r\n 	<li>All-sky visualization in spherical projection</li>\r\n 	<li>grizY and RGB HiPS images for DES releases</li>\r\n 	<li>HiPS images from other suverys like 2MASS, WISE, DSS, SDSS9 as well as extinction and Halpha maps for comparions</li>\r\n 	<li>Visualization of HEALPIX maps</li>\r\n 	<li>Hierarchical overlay of objects</li>\r\n 	<li>Overlay of polygons like DES footprint, tile grid CCDs and healpix grid</li>\r\n 	<li>Search by RA, Dec or tilename</li>\r\n 	<li>Direct link to specific RA, Dec position specified in the URL</li>\r\n 	<li>Export the current view to PNG</li>\r\n 	<li>Access to Tile Viewer</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Mosaic</h2>\r\n<ul class=\"app-paragrafo2\">\r\n 	<li>Mosaic of thumbnails (400 x 400 pixels) for each tile in grizY and RGB for rapid evaluation of features in the co-add images</li>\r\n 	<li>Ability to flag a tile</li>\r\n 	<li>Link to the Tile Viewer</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Tile List</h2>\r\n<ul class=\"app-paragrafo2\">\r\n 	<li>Information for each tile like Tilename, RA, Dec, l, b, and Dataset in a searchable and sortable table</li>\r\n 	<li>Link to the Tile Viewer</li>\r\n</ul>','Sky Viewer','http://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu:8080/dri/apps/sky/','inherit','closed','closed','','6-revision-v1','','','2017-08-11 12:58:03','2017-08-11 15:58:03','',6,'http://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu//6-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(6,1,'2017-06-06 14:33:19','2017-06-06 17:33:19','<b>Objective:</b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sky Viewer allows user to navigate DES footprint for a given release using Aladin where DES images and systematic maps can be displayed. User can also dive into a tile image and examine it using VisiOmatic. At the tile level, images from different data releases (if available at that particular tile) can be compared side by side to perform quality assessment. Both Aladin and VisiOmatic have their native tools available, as well as complementary ones. </span>\r\n\r\n<b>At footprint level (Aladin) :</b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Examine DES images in the footprint as well as related maps (ex. systematics). Use left menu to select what will be displayed, example: tiles, footprint, and layers. You can double-click a tile or center at a given position using the top right form.</span>\r\n\r\n<b>At tile level (VisiOmatic) :</b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Compare images from different releases. Lock position, so both screens show same regions of the sky as you move around.\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Overlay catalogs from DES and other surveys.\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Change image levels to improve contrast. </span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Sky Viewer','https://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu/sky/','publish','closed','closed','','sky-viewer','','','2019-02-04 10:08:40','2019-02-04 12:08:40','',0,'http://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu//?page_id=6',0,'page','',0),(213,1,'2017-12-11 10:03:50','2017-12-11 12:03:50','<b>Objective:</b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sky Viewer allows user to navigate DES footprint for a given release using Aladin where DES images and systematic maps can be displayed. User can also dive into a tile image and examine it using VisiOmatic. At the tile level, images from different data releases (if available at that particular tile) can be compared side by side to perform quality assessment. Both Aladin and VisiOmatic have their native tools available, as well as complementary ones. </span>\r\n\r\n<b>At footprint level (Aladin) :</b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Examine DES images in the footprint as well as related maps (ex. systematics). Use left menu to select what will be displayed, example: tiles, footprint, and layers. You can double-click a tile or center at a given position using the top right form.</span>\r\n\r\n<b>At tile level (VisiOmatic) :</b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Compare images from different releases. Lock position, so both screens show same regions of the sky as you move around.\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Overlay catalogs from DES and other surveys.\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Change image levels to improve contrast. </span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Sky Viewer','https://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu/dri/apps/sky/','inherit','closed','closed','','6-revision-v1','','','2017-12-11 10:03:50','2017-12-11 