ic</strong>\r\n\r\n1. Include coordinates with cursor positioning\r\n2. Allow the user to set a default for Image Preference and use during the session\r\n3. Mantain the crosshair visible in the center of the screen','Release Notes TargetViewer V20170904.01','','inherit','closed','closed','','110-revision-v1','','','2017-08-30 15:50:16','2017-08-30 18:50:16','',110,'http://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu/110-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(112,1,'2017-11-17 15:58:22','2017-11-17 17:58:22','<b>Objective:</b>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Allow user to register and examine a list of targets using DES images. User can sort and filter lists. Targets are organized in classes of objects, like: Galaxy Clusters, Strong Lensing, QSOs, outliers, etc.</span>\n\n<b>Target list level operations:</b>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Add/delete target lists\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Favorite a target list to easily navigate through the lists\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Search target list by name</span>\n\n<b>Target level operations (left side) :</b>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Manage target list content is displayed (e.g. sort columns, lock columns, hide columns)\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Create, save, copy and delete a Target List selection filter (e.g. high-z massive clusters)\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Manipulate Target List items (e.g. rank, reject, and filter)\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Comment Target List items </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Generate and display target list in mosaics in PNG formats  and send e-mail notification to user\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Allow the deletion of the mosaic files</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Allow Target List download. Link is sent via e-mail to user\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Allow Save As of the new target list and send notification to the user\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Allow association between columns of uploaded file and Unified Content Descriptor, for standard analysis of list</span>\n\n<b>At the image level (right side) :</b><b>\n</b>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">VisiOmatic tool is used to display the image\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Display image (element of the target list attached to a tile)</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Rank and reject images\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Add comment to object and position</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Display System and Object Explorer (informations and plots about system or object)\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Crop and download image</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Image display options (show/hide comments, show/hide crosshair, show/hide System Members, etc.)</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">VisiOmatic native features: catalog overlay, image levels, layers, etc.</span>\n<h2>Available Videos</h2>\n<ul>\n 	<li>Comments</li>\n 	<li>Crop</li>\n 	<li>Crop Save</li>\n 	<li>Download part1</li>\n 	<li>Download part2</li>\n 	<li>Filter</li>\n 	<li>Image Preference</li>\n 	<li>Mosaic Presentation</li>\n 	<li>Mosaic Generation</li>\n 	<li>Overlay Catalog</li>\n 	<li>Settings Columns</li>\n 	<li></li>\n</ul>\n[huge_it_videogallery id=\"3\"]','Target Viewer','https://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu/dri/apps/target','inherit','closed','closed','','10-autosave-v1','','','2017-11-17 15:58:22','2017-11-17 17:58:22','',10,'http://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu/10-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(113,1,'2017-08-30 15:53:39','2017-08-30 18:53:39','<strong>Objective:</strong>\r\n\r\nAllow the user to register and observe a list of targets that they want to search from the sky. Each object can have associated coadd images. These lists are organized by the types of elements or form of observation. Ex: Galaxy Clusters, Clusters Members, Strong Lensing, etc...\r\n\r\n<strong>At the general level :</strong>\r\nAdd permanent or temporary target lists\r\nFavorite target list\r\nDelete target list\r\nSearch target list by name\r\n\r\n<strong>At the list level (left side) :</strong>\r\nManage target list (sort columns, lock columns, hide columns, etc...)\r\nAllow to create, save, copy and delete a filter on the target list\r\nAllow to manipulate the target list (rank, reject, filter, etc ...)\r\nInclude comments on target list\r\nGenerate and view target list in mosaics in fits and png formats and send notification to the user\r\nAllow the deletion of the mosaic files\r\nDownload the target list and send notification with link to the user\r\nAllow Save As of the new target list and send notification to the user\r\nAllow association between columns of the file added\r\n\r\n<strong>At the image level (right side) :</strong>\r\nThe VisiOmatic tool is used to display the image\r\nDisplay image (element of the target list attached to a tile)\r\nAllow to rank and reject image\r\nInclude comments on object and position\r\nAllow to display System and Object Explorer information\r\nAllow to crop and download image\r\nAllow to manipulate the image (show/hide commets, show/hide crosshair, show/hide System Members, etc...)\r\nIn VisiOmatic there are some features such as: catalog overlay, select Image Preference, etc ...','Target Viewer','http://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu:8080/dri/apps/target','inherit','closed','closed','','10-revision-v1','','','2017-08-30 15:53:39','2017-08-30 18:53:39','',10,'http://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu/10-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(114,1,'2017-08-31 13:34:43','2017-08-31 16:34:43','<p class=\"app-paragrafo1\">All-sky visualization of DES releases in grizY and RGB with overlay of tile grid and objects <a href=\"http://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu/dri/apps/sky/\" target=\"_self\">click here</a></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"app-paragrafo2\">The main functionalities are:</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Footprint</h2>\r\n<ul class=\"app-paragrafo2\">\r\n 	<li>All-sky visualization in spherical projection</li>\r\n 	<li>grizY and RGB HiPS images for DES releases</li>\r\n 	<li>HiPS images from other suverys like 2MASS, WISE, DSS, SDSS9 as well as extinction and Halpha maps for comparions</li>\r\n 	<li>Visualization of HEALPIX maps</li>\r\n 	<li>Hierarchical overlay of objects</li>\r\n 	<li>Overlay of polygons like DES footprint, tile grid CCDs and healpix grid</li>\r\n 	<li>Search by RA, Dec or tilename</li>\r\n 	<li>Direct link to specific RA, Dec position specified in the URL</li>\r\n 	<li>Export the current view to PNG</li>\r\n 	<li>Access to Tile Viewer</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Mosaic</h2>\r\n<ul class=\"app-paragrafo2\">\r\n 	<li>Mosaic of thumbnails (400 x 400 pixels) for each tile in grizY and RGB for rapid evaluation of features in the co-add images</li>\r\n 	<li>Ability to flag a tile</li>\r\n 	<li>Link to the Tile Viewer</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Tile List</h2>\r\n<ul class=\"app-paragrafo2\">\r\n 	<li>Information for each tile like Tilename, RA, Dec, l, b, and Dataset in a searchable and sortable table</li>\r\n 	<li>Link to the Tile Viewer</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[huge_it_videogallery id=\"2\"]','Sky Viewer','http://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu:8080/dri/apps/sky/','inherit','closed','closed','','6-revision-v1','','','2017-08-31 13:34:43','2017-08-31 16:34:43','',6,'http://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu/6-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(115,1,'2017-08-31 13:54:40','2017-08-31 16:54:40','<strong>Objective:</strong>\r\n\r\nAllow the user to register and observe a list of targets that they want to search from the sky. Each object can have associated coadd images. These lists are organized by the types of elements or form of observation. Ex: Galaxy Clusters, Clusters Members, Strong Lensing, etc...\r\n\r\n<strong>At the general level :</strong>\r\n\r\nAdd permanent or temporary target lists\r\nFavorite target list\r\nDelete target list\r\nSearch target list by name\r\n\r\n<strong>At the list level (left side) :</strong>\r\n\r\nManage target list (sort columns, lock columns, hide columns, etc...)\r\nAllow to create, save, copy and delete a filter on the target list\r\nAllow to manipulate the target list (rank, reject, filter, etc ...)\r\nInclude comments on target list\r\nGenerate and view target list in mosaics in fits and png formats and send notification to the user\r\nAllow the deletion of the mosaic files\r\nDownload the target list and send notification with link to the user\r\nAllow Save As of the new target list and send notification to the user\r\nAllow association between columns of the file added\r\n\r\n<strong>At the image level (right side) :</strong>\r\n\r\nThe VisiOmatic tool is used to display the image\r\nDisplay image (element of the target list attached to a tile)\r\nAllow to rank and reject image\r\nInclude comments on object and position\r\nAllow to display System and Object Explorer information\r\nAllow to crop and download image\r\nAllow to manipulate the image (show/hide commets, show/hide crosshair, show/hide System Members, etc...)\r\nIn VisiOmatic there are some features such as: catalog overlay, select Image Preference, etc ...\r\n\r\n[huge_it_videogallery id=\"3\"]','Target Viewer','http://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu:8080/dri/apps/target','inherit','closed','closed','','10-revision-v1','','','2017-08-31 13:54:40','2017-08-31 16:54:40','',10,'http://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu/10-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(116,1,'2017-09-01 17:29:40','2017-09-01 20:29:40','<strong>Sky Viewer</strong>\r\n\r\n1. Allow global search in both Aladin and Visiomatic\r\n2. Keep zooming when switching from Visiomatic to Aladin\r\n3. Implementation of Catalog Overlay\r\n4. Allow automatic tool change (Aladdin to VisiOmatic) by double click\r\n5. Download original image files in tiff and fits format from Image Viewer\r\n6. Crop of image on VisiOmatic in jpeg format\r\n\r\n<strong>Visiomatic</strong>\r\n\r\n1. Include coordinates with cursor positioning\r\n2. Allow the user to set a default for Image Preference and use during the session\r\n3. Mantain the crosshair visible in the center of the screen\r\n\r\n<strong>Aladin</strong>\r\n\r\n1. Include coordinates with cursor positioning\r\n2. Include the Manage Layers\r\n3. Implementation of Footprint, Depth and Sysmatic maps\r\n\r\n<strong>Depth, Coverge and Systematic Maps</strong>\r\n\r\nThese maps represent a healpixified version of different astronomical variables. Given that each point in the footprint is the combination of information of stacks of images, a statistic has to be used to summarize this information for that particular point. The complex geometry of the survey is kept track through the Mangle software (run by DESDM as an afterburner of the coadd pipeline) and then \"Healpixelized\" to provide the maps made available here.\r\n\r\nThe properties of the maps are: nside=4096, order=nested.\r\n\r\nWe divided those into 3 different classes: depth maps, coverage maps and systematic maps.\r\n\r\n- Depth maps represent the magnitude limit for a given magnitude system as a function of position in the sky, and given a snr ratio. For now, only magnitude limit in 2\'\' (mag_aper4) at 10sigma is present. This is the default variable coming from DESDM, as read from the Mangle products.\r\n- Coverage maps: These maps represent the survey footprint for each band separately, and also for the combination of various bands together, in particular, we present the coverage map for g,r,i,z,Y separately, and another coverage map for the combination of griz and another for grizY.\r\n- Systematic maps: These maps keep track of the spatial variation of several statistics concerning the imaging conditions of the survey across the sky.\r\n\r\n* Detection fraction: what fraction of the Healpix pixel has been observed (according to Mangle geometry) in each band or simultaneously in griz or grizY bands.\r\n* Exposure time: the time in seconds for exposures in a given filter (EXPTIME) or the effective time (TEFF_EXPTIME), weighted with atmospheric transmission, seeing and sky brightness (see here).\r\n* Airmass: secant of the zenith angle for the observations included in the pixel.\r\n* Seeing: measures the sky quality as a blurring of point-like sources, it is described here as the full width half maximum (in arcseconds) of the PSF taken from FWHM_MEAN of the PSF_QA table (calculated using PSFEx). The FLUXRAD quantities are obtained using the flux radius in PSFEx (TBC)\r\n* Sky variance: this is the fluctuation of the sky brightness, weighted using the weight map from DESDM\r\n* Zero point residues from FGCM: residual \"gray\" corrections from FGCM calibration (section 3.3 of the FGCM paper)\r\n\r\nThe statistics used are:\r\n* WAVG: weighted averaged mean of the quantity, considering the noise weight map produced by DESDM\r\n* MIN: minimum of the quantity among all the contributing images.\r\n* MAX: maximum of the quantity among all the contributing images.\r\n* TOTAL, SUM: sum of the quantity for the contributing images.\r\n\r\nAdditional details can be found here:\r\nhttps://cdcvs.fnal.gov/redmine/projects/des-y3/wiki/Y3_systematics_maps_proposed\r\n\r\nand here\r\nhttps://cdcvs.fnal.gov/redmine/projects/des-y3/wiki/systematic_maps','Release Note','','inherit','closed','closed','','107-revision-v1','','','2017-09-01 17:29:40','2017-09-01 20:29:40','',107,'http://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu/107-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(117,1,'2017-09-01 17:29:50','2017-09-01 20:29:50','<strong>Target Viewer</strong>\r\n\r\n1. Implementation of System Explorer\r\n2. Allow bookmarking on target list\r\n3. Include the marker of the object in the image\r\n4. Include the marker of center in the image\r\n5. Include in catalog RA/DEC a popup of object\r\n6. Include comments on list, object and position\r\n7. Download original image files in tiff and fits format\r\n8. Crop of image on VisiOmatic in jpeg format\r\n9. Allow to create, save, copy and delete a filter on the target list\r\n10. Allow to select by rejected in a filter on the target list\r\n11. Generate and view target list in mosaics in fits and png formats and send notification to the user\r\n12. Download the target list and send notification with link to the user\r\n13. Allow Save As of the target list and send notification to the user\r\n14. Allow the deletion of the mosaic files\r\n15. Fix the ellipse problem in the overlay\r\n16. Implementation of Catalog Overlay\r\n\r\n<strong>Visiomatic</strong>\r\n\r\n1. Include coordinates with cursor positioning\r\n2. Allow the user to set a default for Image Preference and use during the session\r\n3. Mantain the crosshair visible in the center of the screen','Release Note','','inherit','closed','closed','','110-revision-v1','','','2017-09-01 17:29:50','2017-09-01 20:29:50','',110,'http://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu/110-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(126,1,'2017-09-15 16:31:51','2017-09-15 19:31:51','<b>Objective:</b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sky Viewer allows user to navigate DES footprint for a given release using Aladin where DES images and systematic maps can be displayed. User can also dive into a tile image and examine it using VisiOmatic. At the tile level, images from different data releases (if available at that particular tile) can be compared side by side to perform quality assessment. Both Aladin and VisiOmatic have their native tools available, as well as complementary ones. </span>\r\n<p class=\"app-paragrafo1\"></p>\r\n<b>At footprint level (Aladin) :</b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Examine DES images in the footprint as well as related maps (ex. systematics). Use left menu to select what will be displayed, example: tiles, footprint, and layers. You can double-click a tile or center at a given position using the top right form, and click Go to examine tile.</span>\r\n<p class=\"app-paragrafo1\"></p>\r\n<b>At tile level (VisiOmatic) :</b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Compare images from different releases. Lock position, so both screens show same regions of the sky as you move around. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Overlay catalogs from DES and other surveys.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Change image levels to improve contrast. </span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Available Videos</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Sky Viewer adjustments</li>\r\n 	<li>Sky Viewer</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[huge_it_videogallery id=\"2\"]','Sky Viewer','http://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu:8080/dri/apps/sky/','inherit','closed','closed','','6-revision-v1','','','2017-09-15 16:31:51','2017-09-15 19:31:51','',6,'http://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu/6-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(118,1,'2017-09-01 17:33:38','2017-09-01 20:33:38','<p class=\"app-paragrafo1\">All-sky visualization of DES releases in grizY and RGB with overlay of tile grid and objects <a href=\"http://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu/dri/apps/sky/\" target=\"_self\">click here</a></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"app-paragrafo2\">The main functionalities are:</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Footprint</h2>\r\n<ul class=\"app-paragrafo2\">\r\n 	<li>All-sky visualization in spherical projection</li>\r\n 	<li>grizY and RGB HiPS images for DES releases</li>\r\n 	<li>HiPS images from other suverys like 2MASS, WISE, DSS, SDSS9 as well as extinction and Halpha maps for comparions</li>\r\n 	<li>Visualization of HEALPIX maps</li>\r\n 	<li>Hierarchical overlay of objects</li>\r\n 	<li>Overlay of polygons like DES footprint, tile grid CCDs and healpix grid</li>\r\n 	<li>Search by RA, Dec or tilename</li>\r\n 	<li>Direct link to specific RA, Dec position specified in the URL</li>\r\n 	<li>Export the current view to PNG</li>\r\n 	<li>Access to Tile Viewer</li>\r\n</