rtal.cosmology.illinois.edu/?p=191',0,'post','',0),(192,1,'2017-11-13 16:09:07','2017-11-13 18:09:07','<ol>\r\n 	<li>Enable Aladin images with proper zoom on Explorer</li>\r\n 	<li>Portal visit statistics: Email contains accumulated month visits.</li>\r\n</ol>','Release v0.12','','inherit','closed','closed','','191-revision-v1','','','2017-11-13 16:09:07','2017-11-13 18:09:07','',191,'http://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu/191-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(133,1,'2017-09-15 17:40:13','2017-09-15 20:40:13','[si-contact-form form=\'1\']','Contact us','','inherit','closed','closed','','84-revision-v1','','','2017-09-15 17:40:13','2017-09-15 20:40:13','',84,'http://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu/84-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(134,1,'2017-09-15 17:40:19','2017-09-15 20:40:19','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">LIneA Science Server</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The LIneA Science Server provide access to the following services: </span>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sky viewer: display a panoramic view of DES images across its footprint.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Target viewer: visualize and manage list of objects. One can rate, filter by properties and export selected objects (for instance, for a observing run).</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">User query: write SQL queries in a web interface to get information from DES NCSA database. </span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Catalog builder: build a catalog…?</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Science products: browse scientific products produce by LIneA Science portal or DES collaboration, such as maps, VACs, and cluster catalogs.</span></li>\r\n</ul>','About us','','inherit','closed','closed','','92-revision-v1','','','2017-09-15 17:40:19','2017-09-15 20:40:19','',92,'http://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu/92-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(136,1,'2017-09-18 10:00:24','2017-09-18 13:00:24','<strong>Objective:</strong>\r\n\r\nAllow the user to register and observe a list of targets that they want to search from the sky. Each object can have associated coadd images. These lists are organized by the types of elements or form of observation. Ex: Galaxy Clusters, Clusters Members, Strong Lensing, etc...\r\n\r\n<strong>At the general level :</strong>\r\n\r\nAdd permanent or temporary target lists\r\nFavorite target list\r\nDelete target list\r\nSearch target list by name\r\n\r\n<strong>At the list level (left side) :</strong>\r\n\r\nManage target list (sort columns, lock columns, hide columns, etc...)\r\nAllow to create, save, copy and delete a filter on the target list\r\nAllow to manipulate the target list (rank, reject, filter, etc ...)\r\nInclude comments on target list\r\nGenerate and view target list in mosaics in fits and png formats and send notification to the user\r\nAllow the deletion of the mosaic files\r\nDownload the target list and send notification with link to the user\r\nAllow Save As of the new target list and send notification to the user\r\nAllow association between columns of the file added\r\n\r\n<strong>At the image level (right side) :</strong>\r\n\r\nThe VisiOmatic tool is used to display the image\r\nDisplay image (element of the target list attached to a tile)\r\nAllow to rank and reject image\r\nInclude comments on object and position\r\nAllow to display System and Object Explorer information\r\nAllow to crop and download image\r\nAllow to manipulate the image (show/hide commets, show/hide crosshair, show/hide System Members, etc...)\r\nIn VisiOmatic there are some features such as: catalog overlay, select Image Preference, etc ...\r\n<h2>Available Videos</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Comments</li>\r\n 	<li>Crop</li>\r\n 	<li>Crop Save</li>\r\n 	<li>Download part1</li>\r\n 	<li>Download part2</li>\r\n 	<li>Filter</li>\r\n 	<li>Image Preference</li>\r\n 	<li>Mosaic Presentation</li>\r\n 	<li>Mosaic Generation</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[huge_it_videogallery id=\"3\"]','Target Viewer','https://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu:8080/dri/apps/target','inherit','closed','closed','','10-revision-v1','','','2017-09-18 10:00:24','2017-09-18 13:00:24','',10,'http://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu/10-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(137,1,'2017-09-18 10:00:49','2017-09-18 13:00:49','[embed]https://youtu.be/7VfilGzeCyg[/embed]\r\n<p class=\"app-paragrafo1\">Browse products created by the portal and collaboration. <a href=\"http://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu/dri/apps/products\" target=\"_self\">click here</a></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul class=\"app-paragrafo2\">\r\n 	<li>Filter by Release (e.g. Y1 Wide Survey), Dataset (e.g. S82), or Type (e.g. Targets, VACs, Masks)</li>\r\n 	<li>Order and filter list of products by attributes (e.g. Type, Name, Owner)</li>\r\n</ul>','Science Products','https://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu:8080/dri/apps/products','inherit','closed','closed','','14-revision-v1','','','2017-09-18 10:00:49','2017-09-18 13:00:49','',14,'http://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu/14-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(138,1,'2017-09-18 13:26:37','2017-09-18 16:26:37','<b>Sky Viewer</b>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Allow global search in both Aladin and Visiomatic </span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Keep zooming when switching from Visiomatic to Aladin </span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Implementation of Catalog Overlay </span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Allow automatic tool change (Aladdin to VisiOmatic) by double click </span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Download original image files in tiff and fits format from Image Viewer</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Crop of image on VisiOmatic in jpeg format</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<b>Aladin</b>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Include coordinates with cursor positioning </span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Implementation of Depth, Coverage and Systematic Maps</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<b>Visiomatic</b>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Include coordinates with cursor positioning </span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Allow the user to set a default for Image Preference and use during the session</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<b>Depth, Coverage and Systematic Maps</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">These maps represent a Healpix version of different astronomical properties distribution across the sky. Given that each point in the footprint is the combination of information of stacks of images, a statistic has to be used to summarize this information for that particular point. The complex geometry of the survey is kept track through the Mangle software (run by DESDM as an afterburner of the coadd pipeline) and then \"Healpixelized\" to provide the maps made available here.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The properties of the maps are: nside=4096, order=nested.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We divided those into 3 different classes: depth maps, coverage maps and systematic maps.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">- Depth maps represent the magnitude limit for a given magnitude system as a function of position in the sky, and given a snr ratio. For now, only magnitude limit in 2\'\' (mag_aper4) at 10sigma is present. This is the default variable coming from DESDM, as read from the Mangle products.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">- Coverage maps: These maps represent the survey footprint for each band separately, and also for the combination of various bands together, in particular, we present the coverage map for g,r,i,z,Y separately, and another coverage map for the combination of griz and another for grizY.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> - Systematic maps: These maps keep track of the spatial variation of several statistics concerning the imaging conditions of the survey across the sky.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">   * Detection fraction: what fraction of the Healpix pixel has been observed (according to Mangle geometry) in each band or simultaneously in griz or grizY bands.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">   * Exposure time: the time in seconds for exposures in a given filter (EXPTIME) or the effective time (TEFF_EXPTIME), weighted with atmospheric transmission, seeing and sky brightness (see here).</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">   * Airmass: secant of the zenith angle for the observations included in the pixel.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">   * Seeing: measures the sky quality as a blurring of point-like sources, it is described here as the full width half maximum (in arcseconds) of the PSF taken from FWHM_MEAN of the PSF_QA table (calculated using PSFEx). The FLUXRAD quantities are obtained using the flux radius in PSFEx (TBC)</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">   * Sky variance: this is the fluctuation of the</span> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">sky brightness, weighted using the weight map from DESDM</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">   * Zero point residues from FGCM: residual \"gray\" corrections from FGCM calibration (section 3.3 of the FGCM paper)</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The statistics used are:</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">   * WAVG: weighted averaged mean of the quantity, considering the noise weight map produced by DESDM</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">   * MIN: minimum of the quantity among all the contributing images.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">   * MAX: maximum of the quantity among all the contributing images.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">   * TOTAL, SUM: sum of the quantity for the contributing images.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Additional details can be found here:</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><a href=\"https://cdcvs.fnal.gov/redmine/projects/des-y3/wiki/Y3_systematics_maps_proposed\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">https://cdcvs.fnal.gov/redmine/projects/des-y3/wiki/Y3_systematics_maps_proposed</span></a>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">and here</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><a href=\"https://cdcvs.fnal.gov/redmine/projects/des-y3/wiki/systematic_maps\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">https://cdcvs.fnal.gov/redmine/projects/des-y3/wiki/systematic_maps</span></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Release Note','','inherit','closed','closed','','107-autosave-v1','','','2017-09-18 13:26:37','2017-09-18 16:26:37','',107,'http://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu/107-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(139,1,'2017-09-18 13:27:41','2017-09-18 16:27:41','<b>Sky Viewer</b>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Allow global search in both Aladin and Visiomatic </span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Keep zooming when switching from Visiomatic to Aladin </span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Implementation of Catalog Overlay </span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Allow automatic tool change (Aladdin to VisiOmatic) by double click </span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Download original image files in tiff and fits format from Image Viewer</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Crop of image on VisiOmatic in jpeg format</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<b>Aladin</b>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Include coordinates with cursor positioning </span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Implementation of Depth, Coverage and Systematic Maps</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<b>Visiomatic</b>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Include coordinates with cursor positioning </span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Allow the user to set a default for Image Preference and use during the session</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<b>Depth, Coverage and Systematic Maps</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">These maps represent a Healpix version of different astronomical properties distribution across the sky. Given that each point in the footprint is the combination of information of stacks of images, a statistic has to be used to summarize this information for that particular point. The complex geometry of the survey is kept track through the Mangle software (run by DESDM as an afterburner of the coadd pipeline) and then \"Healpixelized\" to provide the maps made available here.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The properties of the maps are: nside=4096, order=nested.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We divided those into 3 different classes: depth maps, coverage maps and systematic maps.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">- Depth maps represent the magnitude limit for a given magnitude system as a function of position in the sky, and given a snr ratio. For now, only magnitude limit in 2\'\' (mag_aper4) at 10sigma is present. This is the default variable coming from DESDM, as read from the Mangle products.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">- Coverage maps: These maps represent the survey footprint for each band separately, and also for the combination of various bands together, in particular, we present the coverage map for g,r,i,z,Y separately, and another coverage map for the combination of griz and another for grizY.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> - Systematic maps: These maps keep track of the spatial variation of several statistics concerning the imaging conditions of the survey across the sky.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">   * Detection fraction: what fraction of the Healpix pixel has been observed (according to Mangle geometry) in each band or simultaneously in griz or grizY bands.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">   * Exposure time: the time in seconds for exposures in a given filter (EXPTIME) or the effective time (TEFF_EXPTIME), weighted with atmospheric transmission, seeing and sky brightness (see here).</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">   * Airmass: secant of the zenith angle for the observations included in the pixel.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">   * Seeing: measures the sky quality as a blurring of point-like sources, it is described here as the full width half maximum (in arcseconds) of the PSF taken from FWHM_MEAN of the PSF_QA table (calculated using PSFEx). The FLUXRAD quantities are obtained using the flux radius in PSFEx (TBC)</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">   * Sky variance: this is the fluctuation of the</span> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">sky brightness, weighted using the weight map from DESDM</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">   * Zero point residues from FGCM: residual \"gray\" corrections from FGCM calibration (section 3.3 of the FGCM paper)</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The statistics used are:</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">   * WAVG: weighted averaged mean of the quantity, considering the noise weight map produced by DESDM</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">   * MIN: minimum of the quantity among all the contributing images.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">   * MAX: maximum of the quantity among all the contributing images.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">   * TOTAL, SUM: sum of the quantity for the contributing images.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Additional details can be found here:</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><a href=\"https://cdcvs.fnal.gov/redmine/projects/des-y3/wiki/Y3_systematics_maps_proposed\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">https://cdcvs.fnal.gov/redmine/projects/des-y3/wiki/Y3_systematics_maps_proposed</span></a>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">and here</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><a href=\"https://cdcvs.fnal.gov/redmine/projects/des-y3/wiki/systematic_maps\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">https://cdcvs.fnal.gov/redmine/projects/des-y3/wiki/systematic_maps</span></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Release Note','','inherit','closed','closed','','107-revision-v1','','','2017-09-18 13:27:41','2017-09-18 16:27:41','',107,'http://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu/107-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(140,1,'2017-09-18 13:28:47','2017-09-18 16:28:47','<b>Target Viewer</b>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Favorite Target List </span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pinpoint object in image</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pinpoint center in image</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Display the RA / DEC information of the object in the catalog pop-up</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ability to comment list, object, and position </span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Download image files in TIFF and FITS format </span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Crop VisiOmatic image in JPEG format</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Create custom selection filters on Target List</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Allow to select by no rejected object in a filter on the target list</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Generate cutouts in PNG format for target lists and display as a mosaic.  User is notified via email. Cutouts can be deleted.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Download filtered target list and send email with link to user </span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Allow Save As a new target list and send notification to the user </span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Implementation of Catalog Overlay </span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Fix ellipse problem in Catalog Overlay</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<b>VisiOmatic</b>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Include coordinates with cursor positioning </span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Allow user to setup a new Image Preference as default during session</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;','Release Note','','inherit','closed','closed','','110-revision-v1','','','2017-09-18 13:28:47','2017-09-18 16:28:47','',110,'http://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu/110-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(141,1,'2017-09-18 13:30:30','2017-09-18 16:30:30','<b>Objective:</b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Allow the user to register and observe a list of targets that they want to search from the sky. Each object can have associated coadd images. These lists are organized by the types of elements or form of observation. Ex: Galaxy Clusters, Clusters Members, Strong Lensing, etc...</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>At the general level :</b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Add permanent or temporary target lists </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Favorite target list</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Delete target list</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Search target list by name</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>At the list level (left side) :</b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Manage target list (sort columns, lock columns, hide columns, etc...)</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Allow Save As of the new target list and send notification to the user</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Download the target list and send notification with link to the user </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Include comments on target list </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Generate and view target list in mosaics in png formats  and send notification to the user</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Allow the deletion of the mosaic files</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Allow to manipulate the target list (rank, reject, filter, etc ...)</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Allow association between columns of the file added </span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>At the image level (right side) :</b><b>\r\n</b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The VisiOmatic tool is used to display the image </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Display image (element of the target list attached to a tile)</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Allow to rank and reject image</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Include comments on object and position</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Allow to crop and download image</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Allow to manipulate the image (show/hide commets, show/hide crosshair, show/hide System Members, etc...)</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In VisiOmatic there are some features such as: catalog overlay, select Image Preference, etc...</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Target Viewer','https://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu:8080/dri/apps/target','inherit','closed','closed','','10-revision-v1','','','2017-09-18 13:30:30','2017-09-18 16:30:30','',10,'http://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu/10-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(142,1,'2017-09-18 13:40:34','2017-09-18 16:40:34','<b><i>About LIneA</i></b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Laboratório Interinstitucional de e-Astronomia (LIneA) was created in November 2010 by an agreement signed by three research institutes of the Ministry of Science, Technology, Innovation and Communication (MCTIC) (Laboratório Nacional de Computação Científica, Observatório Nacional,  e  Rede Nacional de Ensino e Pesquisa) to provide support for the participation of Brazilian scientists in large international programs requiring an IT infrastructure such as SDSS, DES, DESI and LSST. Some of its main projects include:</span>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Quick Reduce pipeline available at CTIO to assess the quality of the images gathered by DECam; </span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Science Portal, a comprehensive integrated web-based end-to-end system to streamline the production of ancillary information used to create value-added science ready catalog to feed a variety of science analysis workflows;</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Data Server interface available at Fermilab since April 2014 to enable the visualization of images and objects, and to carry out queries in the DESDM database. The interface has been accessed 4500 times over the past three years by 250 users;</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Quick Look Framework (QLF) being developed to assess the quality of the 15,000 spectra of the 5,000 objects to be observed in each exposure of DESI.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The LIneA Science Server being made available at NCSA and which will be used as one of the interfaces of the DES data release DR1.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In addition, LIneA maintains a data center (1000 cores processing cluster, 1 PB mass storage and a host of other machines) for its affiliates, currently around 80 members, a mirror site for SDSS providing independent SkyServer and CasJobs services, and provides support to the computer infrastructure being used by the APOGEE-2 project at the Las Campanas Observatory.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">LIneA is funded by MCTIC, FINEP and </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Fundação de Amparo à Pesquisa do Estado do Rio de Janeiro</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> - </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">FAPERJ</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.</span>\r\n\r\n<b><i>About the LIneA Science Server Interface</i></b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Currently the LIneA Science Server provides access to the following services:</span>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sky viewer: display a panoramic view of DES images across its footprint.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Target viewer: visualize and manage list of objects. One can rank,  reject entries filter by properties, and create mosaics.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Science products: browse scientific products produce by LIneA Science portal or DES collaboration, such as maps, VACs, and cluster catalogs.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In the future we expect it to also provide</span>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">User query: write SQL queries in a web interface to get information from DES NCSA database.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Catalog builder: build a catalog using the framework presented in Fausti et al.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b><i>Credits</i></b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We would like to thank the contribution of the following people and organizations:</span>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">NCSA team for providing the infrastructure and tools such as which are use by Science Server </span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">E. Bertin for the use of  VisiOmatic and for helping in its installation</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">P. Fernique for helping in the integration of Aladin in the Science Server framework</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">LIneA team:</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Luiz Nicolaci da Costa (Lead Scientist)</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Angelo Fausti Neto (Technical Lead)</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Glauber Rocha</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Riccardo Campisano</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Rafael</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Fabio Oliveira</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-