6:48:48','2017-09-18 19:48:48','<b>Objective:</b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Allow user to register and examine a list of targets using DES images. User can sort and filter lists. Targets are organized in classes of objects, like: Galaxy Clusters, Strong Lensing, QSOs, outliers, etc.</span>\r\n\r\n<b>Target list level operations:</b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Add/delete target lists\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Favorite a target list to easily navigate through the lists\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Search target list by name</span>\r\n\r\n<b>Target level operations (left side) :</b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Manage now target list content is displayed (ex. sort columns, lock columns, hide columns)\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Create, save, copy and delete a Target List selection filter (ex. high-z massive clusters)\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Manipulate Target List items (ex. rank, reject, and filter)\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Comment Target List items </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Generate and display target list in mosaics in PNG formats  and send e-mail notification to user\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Allow the deletion of the mosaic files</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Allow Target List download. Link is sent via e-mail to user\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Allow Save As of the new target list and send notification to the user\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Allow association between columns of uploaded file and Unified Content Descriptor, for standard analysis of list</span>\r\n\r\n<b>At the image level (right side) :</b>\r\n\r\n<b>\r\n</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">VisiOmatic tool is used to display the image\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Display image (element of the target list attached to a tile)</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Rank and reject images\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Add comment to object and position</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Display System and Object Explorer (informations and plots about system or object)\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Crop and download image</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Image display options (show/hide comments, show/hide crosshair, show/hide System Members, etc...)</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">VisiOmatic native features: catalog overlay, image levels, layers, etc.</span>\r\n<h2>Available Videos</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Comments</li>\r\n 	<li>Crop</li>\r\n 	<li>Crop Save</li>\r\n 	<li>Download part1</li>\r\n 	<li>Download part2</li>\r\n 	<li>Filter</li>\r\n 	<li>Image Preference</li>\r\n 	<li>Mosaic Presentation</li>\r\n 	<li>Mosaic Generation</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[huge_it_videogallery id=\"3\"]','Target Viewer','https://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu:8080/dri/apps/target','inherit','closed','closed','','10-revision-v1','','','2017-09-18 16:48:48','2017-09-18 19:48:48','',10,'http://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu/10-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(149,1,'2017-09-18 16:56:06','2017-09-18 19:56:06','<b><i>About LIneA</i></b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Laboratório Interinstitucional de e-Astronomia (LIneA) was created in November 2010 by an agreement signed by three research institutes of the Ministry of Science, Technology, Innovation and Communication (MCTIC) (Laboratório Nacional de Computação Científica, Observatório Nacional,  e  Rede Nacional de Ensino e Pesquisa) to provide support for the participation of Brazilian scientists in large international programs requiring an IT infrastructure such as SDSS, DES, DESI and LSST. Some of its main projects include:</span>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Quick Reduce pipeline available at CTIO to assess the quality of the images gathered by DECam; </span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Science Portal, a comprehensive integrated web-based end-to-end system to streamline the production of ancillary information used to create value-added science ready catalog to feed a variety of science analysis workflows;</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Data Server interface available at Fermilab since April 2014 to enable the visualization of images and objects, and to carry out queries in the DESDM database. The interface has been accessed 4500 times over the past three years by 250 users;</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Quick Look Framework (QLF) being developed to assess the quality of the 15,000 spectra of the 5,000 objects to be observed in each exposure of DESI.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The LIneA Science Server being made available at NCSA and which will be used as one of the interfaces of the DES data release DR1.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In addition, LIneA maintains a data center (1000 cores processing cluster, 1 PB mass storage and a host of other machines) for its affiliates, currently around 80 members, a mirror site for SDSS providing independent SkyServer and CasJobs services, and provides support to the computer infrastructure being used by the APOGEE-2 project at the Las Campanas Observatory.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">LIneA is funded by MCTIC, FINEP and </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Fundação de Amparo à Pesquisa do Estado do Rio de Janeiro</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> - </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">FAPERJ</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.</span>\r\n\r\n<b><i>About the LIneA Science Server Interface</i></b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Currently the LIneA Science Server provides access to the following services:</span>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sky viewer: display a panoramic view of DES images across its footprint.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Target viewer: visualize and manage list of objects. One can rank,  reject entries filter by properties, and create mosaics.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Science products: browse scientific products produce by LIneA Science portal or DES collaboration, such as maps, VACs, and cluster catalogs.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In the future we expect it to also provide</span>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">User query: write SQL queries in a web interface to get information from DES NCSA database.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Catalog builder: build a catalog using the framework presented in Fausti et al.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b><i>Credits</i></b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We would like to thank the contribution of the following people and organizations:</span>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">NCSA team for providing the infrastructure and tools such as which are use by Science Server </span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">E. Bertin for the use of  VisiOmatic and for helping in its installation</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">P. Fernique for helping in the integration of Aladin in the Science Server framework</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">LIneA team:</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Luiz Nicolaci da Costa (Lead Scientist)</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Angelo Fausti Neto (Technical Lead)</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Glauber Costa</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Riccardo Campisano</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Rafael Brito</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Fabio Oliveira</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Felipe Machado </span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ricardo Ogando</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Guilherme Soares</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Cida Silveira</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Maria Luiza Sanchez</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Humberto Aranha</span></li>\r\n</ul>','About us','','inherit','closed','closed','','92-revision-v1','','','2017-09-18 16:56:06','2017-09-18 19:56:06','',92,'http://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu/92-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(150,1,'2017-09-19 16:24:19','2017-09-19 19:24:19','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This is the release of beta version release of the LIneA Science Server which is a modernized version of the system running at Fermilab since 2014.  The main goals of this development was to introduce newer technology using the extJS framework with django instead of turbogears, each tool is independent facilitating deployment of new features and bug fixes, and easy access to images and catalogs by making it available at NCSA.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">As announced to the collaboration the Fermilab version was frozen in January 2016, while a preliminary version of the new system has been running at NCSA since June 2016 to enable people to visualize the data from Y3 with the last update taking place 06/14/2017.  Since then 631 commits have been made, 1752 files modified, 54708 lines added and 160646 removed involving a number of people in LIneA´s IT team. A complete list of in-house and external contributors can be found in </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">About us</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> section.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The current version is for the use of the DES collaboration members and following tools are available: sky viewer, target viewer and science products. These are the ones intended to become available for the general public in December but connected to separate tables been created by the NCSA team. In parallel, we are also developing user query an upgraded version of the one available at Fermilab but scarcely used which will be integrated to the Target Viewer greatly simplifying the life of the user.  In a longer timescale is also envisioned the deployment of  a catalog builder tool using the infrastructure developed for the Science Portal and presented in the last portal review (DES-doc-10898-v1) and part of the paper Fausti et al  (DES-doc-9416-v9). </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The current system is still a work in progress and we call on users to provide feedback to the team using the contact us form which will send a classified ticket to LIneA´s helpdesk facilitating tracking them down. We hope that this will allow us to shake down bugs in preparation for the public release next December. We will also continue to improve the tutorial videos by including some text, updating some of them and including new ones to cover all the features normally used.</span>\r\n\r\nThere are some known bugs or inconvenient features:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>We have implemented a social log in to serve as an example of what will be used in the public release. Currently, for tests we keep a white list to prevent access from unauthorized users;</li>\r\n 	<li>The number of objects in a list is not correct The quick upload only works if the format of the example is used even minor departures will cause an error</li>\r\n 	<li>We are aware of problems handling objects close to ra =0</li>\r\n 	<li>We are currently limiting the number of cutouts to tem to serve as an example</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThese problems are currently being addressed by our team and we expect to have another quick release as soon as possible. As soon as the environment becomes a bit more stable more tutorial videos will be produced.','Preliminary Release of the LIneA Science Server','','publish','open','open','','preliminary-release-of-the-linea-science-server','','','2017-09-25 14:18:31','2017-09-25 17:18:31','',0,'http://desportal.cosmology.illinois.edu/?p=150',0,'post','',0),(151,1,'2017-09-19 16:24:19','2017-09-19 19:24:19','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This is the release of beta version release of the LIneA Science Server which is a modernized version of the system running at Fermilab since 2014.  The main goals of this development was to introduce newer technology using the extJS framework instead of turbogears, each tool is independent facilitating deployment of new features and bug fixes, and easy access to images and catalogs by making it available at NCSA.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">As announced to the collaboration the Fermilab version was frozen in 2015, while a preliminary version of the new system has been running at NCSA since xxx to enable people to visualize the data from Y3 with the last update taking place 06/14/2017.  Since then 631 commits have been made, 1752 files modified, 54708 lines added and 160646 removed involving a number of people in LIn